            text: "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t<strong>**be** 动词&nbsp;</strong></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t**be** 动词有两种过去时形式：**was** 和 **were**。代词 **he**、**she**、**it** 和 **I** 使用 **was**，**you**、**we** 和 **they** 使用 **were**。&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 5%;\">\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/82/08/v/108208/GE_4.3.1.2.2_1_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\n\t\t\t\t<em>He <strong>was</strong> tired yesterday.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em></td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"width: 1%;\">\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"width: 54%;\">\n\t\t\t\t他昨天很累。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 5%;\">\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/82/09/v/108209/GE_4.3.1.2.2_2_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\n\t\t\t\t<em>They <strong>were</strong> happy in Paris.</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"width: 1%;\">\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t他们以前在巴黎过得很开心。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t<strong>否定式</strong></td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t使用  **did + not** 来组成动词过去时否定式。主要动词保持原形。&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 5%;\">\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/82/10/v/108210/GE_4.3.1.2.2_3_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\n\t\t\t\t<em>They <strong>did not like </strong>London.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"width: 1%;\">\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"width: 54%;\">\n\t\t\t\t他们以前不喜欢伦敦。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\">\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/82/11/v/108211/GE_4.3.1.2.2_4_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\">\n\t\t\t\t<em>We <strong>did not meet </strong>John yesterday.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t我们昨天没有碰到 John。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"6\">\n\t\t\t\t在英语口语中，短语 **did + not** 通常缩写为 **didn't**。&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 5%;\">\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/82/12/v/108212/GE_4.3.1.2.2_5_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\">\n\t\t\t\t<em>They <strong>didn&#39;t </strong>like London.</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t他们以前不喜欢伦敦。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\">\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/82/13/v/108213/GE_4.3.1.2.2_6_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"2\">\n\t\t\t\t<em>We <strong>didn&#39;t </strong>meet John yesterday.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t我们昨天没有碰到 John。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>",
