            text: '<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%;" width="700">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t<strong>&#39;Anyway</strong>&#39;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t使用单词 **anyway** 来结束或总结话题，这样一来你可以开始一个新话题。当你听厌了某人谈论某事，非常想改变话题时，就可以使用这个词。</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style="width: 5%;">\n\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/84/55/v/108455/GE_4.3.2.4.1_3_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t<td style="width: 40%;">\n\t\t\t\tA: <em>That restaurant wasn&#39;t very good.</em><br />\n\t\t\t\tB:<em> No, it wasn&#39;t! The meat tasted bad, and the salad wasn&#39;t fresh. And the waiter was awful! His clothes were dirty!</em><br />\n\t\t\t\tA: <em><strong>Anyway</strong>, we&#39;re not going there again. So, how&#39;s Jane?</em></td>\n\t\t\t<td style="width: 50%;">\n\t\t\t\t那家餐馆不是很好。<br />\n\t\t\t\t是啊，不怎么好！肉有味道，沙拉也不新鲜。而且服务员也很差劲！他的衣服很脏！<br />\n\t\t\t\t总之，我们不打算再去了。对了，Jane 还好吧？</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>',
