            text: '<div>\n\t<strong>可能性副词</strong><br />\n\t<br />\n\t<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%;" width="700">\n\t\t<tbody>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t\t可能性副词表示某事发生的相对可能性。<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t\t副词通常直接位于其修饰的动词之前，如果是 **be** 动词，则位于其后。**maybe** 是例外，常常位于句首。<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t\t表示百分之百的可能性，使用 **definitely** 或 **absolutely**。<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/99/40/v/109940/GE_4.5.1.3.2_1_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<em>I <strong>definitely</strong> saw Sheila at the party.</em></td>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t（我肯定在派对上看到了 Sheila。）&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/99/41/v/109941/GE_4.5.1.3.2_2_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<em>Lucille <strong>absolutely </strong>can&#39;t come.</em></td>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t（Lucille 绝对不能来。）</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td colspan="3">\n\t\t\t\t\t<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t表示较大的可能性，使用 **probably**。<br />\n\t\t\t\t\t&nbsp;</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/99/42/v/109942/GE_4.5.1.3.2_3_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<em>They are <strong>probably</strong> late.</em></td>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t（他们很可能迟到了。）</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/99/43/v/109943/GE_4.5.1.3.2_4_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t<em>Dylan <strong>probably</strong> brought drinks.</em></td>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t（Dylan 很可能带了酒水。）</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t\t<td style="width: 5%;">\n\t\t\t\t\thttps://cns2.ef-cdn.com/Juno/10/99/44/v/109944/GE_4.5.1.3.2_5_v2.mp3</td>\n\t\t\t\t<td style="width: 40%;">\n\t\t\t\t\t<em>They <strong>probably</strong> can&#39;t buy snacks.</em></td>\n\t\t\t\t<td>\n\t\t\t\t\t（他们很可能不能买零食。）</td>\n\t\t\t</tr>\n\t\t</tbody>\n\t</table>\n</div>\n<p>\n\t&nbsp;</p>',
